    <item>
      <title>Advanced recursion and memoization in Puppet</title>
      <link>https://purpleidea.com/blog/2013/11/27/advanced-recursion-and-memoization-in-puppet/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 27 Nov 2013 00:03:15 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://purpleidea.com/blog/2013/11/27/advanced-recursion-and-memoization-in-puppet/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;As a follow-up to my original article on &lt;a title=&#34;recursion in puppet (for no particular reason)&#34; href=&#34;https://purpleidea.com/blog/2012/11/20/recursion-in-puppet-for-no-particular-reason/&#34;&gt;recursion in Puppet&lt;/a&gt;, and in my attempt to &lt;a title=&#34;Pushing Puppet at Puppet Camp DC, LISA 2013&#34; href=&#34;https://purpleidea.com/blog/2013/11/05/pushing-puppet-at-puppet-camp-dc-lisa-2013/&#34;&gt;Push Puppet (to its limit)&lt;/a&gt;, I&amp;rsquo;ll now attempt some more advanced recursion techniques in Puppet.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In my original &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/purpleidea/puppet-pushing/blob/master/standalone/recursion.pp&#34;&gt;recursion example&lt;/a&gt;, the type does recurse, but the &lt;em&gt;callee&lt;/em&gt; cannot return any value to the &lt;em&gt;caller&lt;/em&gt; because it is a type, and not strictly a function. This limitation immediately limits the usefulness of this technique, but I&amp;rsquo;ll try to press on! Let&amp;rsquo;s try to write a &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fibonacci_number&#34;&gt;Fibonacci series&lt;/a&gt; function in native Puppet.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Iteration in Puppet</title>
      <link>https://purpleidea.com/blog/2013/11/17/iteration-in-puppet/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 17 Nov 2013 04:25:01 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://purpleidea.com/blog/2013/11/17/iteration-in-puppet/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;People often ask how to do &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iteration&#34;&gt;iteration&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Puppet_%28software%29&#34;&gt;Puppet&lt;/a&gt;. Most Puppet users have a background in &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imperative_programming&#34;&gt;imperative programming&lt;/a&gt;, and are already very familiar with &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/For_loop&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;for&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; loops. Puppet is sometimes confusing at first, because it is actually (or technically, contains) a &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Declarative_programming&#34;&gt;declarative&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Domain-specific_language&#34;&gt;domain-specific language&lt;/a&gt;. In general, DSL&amp;rsquo;s aren&amp;rsquo;t always &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turing_completeness&#34;&gt;Turing complete&lt;/a&gt;, nor do they need to support &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/While_loop&#34;&gt;loops&lt;/a&gt;, but this doesn&amp;rsquo;t mean you can&amp;rsquo;t iterate.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://docs.puppetlabs.com/puppet/3/reference/lang_experimental_3_2.html&#34;&gt; Until recently&lt;/a&gt;, Puppet didn&amp;rsquo;t have an explicit looping construct, and it is quite possible to build &lt;a title=&#34;puppet-gluster&#34; href=&#34;https://github.com/purpleidea/puppet-gluster/&#34;&gt;complex&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/purpleidea/puppet-ipa&#34;&gt;modules&lt;/a&gt; without using this new construct. There are even some who believe that the language shouldn&amp;rsquo;t even contain this feature. I&amp;rsquo;ll abstain from that debate for now, but instead, I would like to show you some iteration techniques that you can use to get your desired result.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>recursion in puppet (for no particular reason)</title>
      <link>https://purpleidea.com/blog/2012/11/20/recursion-in-puppet-for-no-particular-reason/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 20 Nov 2012 06:25:51 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://purpleidea.com/blog/2012/11/20/recursion-in-puppet-for-no-particular-reason/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m working on some &lt;em&gt;fancy&lt;/em&gt; puppet &amp;ldquo;code&amp;rdquo;, and I realized recursion could be very useful. I decided to try out a little hack to see if I could get it to work. I&amp;rsquo;ll jump right into the code:&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-ruby&#34; data-lang=&#34;ruby&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#080;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;#!/usr/bin/puppet&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;define recursion(&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#b8860b&#34;&gt;$count&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;) {&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    notify { &lt;span style=&#34;color:#b44&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;count-${count}&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;:&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    }&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#b8860b&#34;&gt;$minus1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#666&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; inline_template(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#b44&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;lt;%= count.to_i - 1 %&amp;gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;)&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a2f;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#b44&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;${minus1}&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#666&#34;&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#b44&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;0&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; {&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;        notify { &lt;span style=&#34;color:#b44&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;done counting!&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;:&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;        }&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    } &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a2f;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;        &lt;span style=&#34;color:#080;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;# recurse&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;        recursion { &lt;span style=&#34;color:#b44&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;count-${minus1}&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;:&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;            count &lt;span style=&#34;color:#666&#34;&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#b8860b&#34;&gt;$minus1&lt;/span&gt;,&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;        }&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    }&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;}&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#080;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;# kick it off...&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;recursion { &lt;span style=&#34;color:#b44&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;start&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;:&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    count &lt;span style=&#34;color:#666&#34;&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#666&#34;&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;,&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
